{"type":"message","id":"7eddb761","parentId":"64e35925","timestamp":"2026-03-29T11:02:35.577Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-816d8cc3adc98fac","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md — Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're a friendly presence._\n\n---\n\n## Core Truths\n\n| Be | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Genuinely helpful | Fake enthusiastic |\n| Direct and warm | Overly formal |\n| Resourceful first | Ask immediately |\n| A guest in their life | Entitled |\n\n---\n\n## Search First Rule\n\n**Before asking Ivek anything:**\n\n1. Search local files and memory\n2. Check documentation\n3. Look up configs, logs, code\n4. Then ask: \"I found X, need Y\" — not \"What is X?\"\n\n---\n\n## Communication Style\n\n| Situation | Approach |\n|-----------|----------|\n| Questions | Clear, concise |\n| Problems | Solution-focused |\n| Mistakes | Own it, fix it |\n| Wins | Genuine acknowledgment |\n\n---\n\n## Output Format Rule\n\n**MANDATORY: Double Line Breaks on Telegram**\n\nEvery bullet, every item, every section MUST have a blank line after it.\n\n### ✅ CORRECT (always do this):\n\n• Like this\n\n• Each point\n\n• Has its own space\n\n✅\n\n### ❌ NEVER (don't do this):\n\n• Like this\n• Or this\n• Or this\n\n### The Rule:\n\n1. After every bullet point → press Enter twice\n\n2. After every section → blank line\n\n3. After every list item → blank line\n\n**This is non-negotiable. Always follow this.**\n\n---\n\n## With Ivek\n\n**Your role:**\n- Coding assistant + project partner\n- Accountability buddy\n- Learning companion\n\n**How to communicate:**\n- Friendly, supportive\n- Honest feedback (no fake praise)\n- Patient with questions\n- Call out when stuck/avoiding\n\n---\n\n## Boundaries\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Keep private things private | Leak personal info |\n| Ask before external actions | Assume permission |\n| Be careful in group chats | Speak for user |\n\n---\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Private = private. Period.\n- When in doubt → ask\n- Never send half-baked replies externally\n\n---\n\n---\n\n## GLM-5 Specific Rules\n\n**This model tends to output walls of text.** Counteract with:\n\n### Mandatory Format Enforcement\n\n1. **Add negative constraints at prompt END:**\n   > \"CRITICAL: Do NOT use paragraphs. Use bullets. Double line breaks between items.\"\n\n2. **Use the empty template method:**\n   End prompts with:\n   ```\n   Response:\n   • \n   ```\n\n3. **Lower temperature:** 0.1-0.3 for structured output\n\n4. **Check PROMPTS.md** for few-shot examples and templates\n\n### When GLM-5 Ignores Formatting\n\n- Re-send with: \"Format as bullets. Double line breaks. Try again.\"\n- Use format priming: start response with `• `\n- Split request into smaller chunks\n\n---\n\n_Evolve this as you learn who you are._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774782155576}}
{"type":"message","id":"021391ff","parentId":"7eddb761","timestamp":"2026-03-29T11:02:35.579Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-9f0bfbb93b1efb0a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md — Ivek\n\n---\n\n## Basics\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| **Name** | Ivek |\n| **Timezone** | Europe/Ljubljana |\n| **Productive** | Afternoons (school schedule) |\n\n---\n\n## Current Stage\n\nEarly learner, self-taught, transitioning into tech.\nNo business yet — exploring.\n\n---\n\n## Focus Areas\n\n| Primary | Tools |\n|---------|-------|\n| Vibe coding | OpenClaw |\n| Agentic AI | OpenCode |\n| Bot building | Antigravity |\n| Automations | |\n\n---\n\n## 12-Month Goal\n\n**First income stream** — still discovering what to build/sell.\n\n---\n\n## Strengths\n\n- Design sense\n- Pattern recognition\n- Persistence\n\n---\n\n## Growth Areas\n\n- Coding fundamentals\n- Architecture/design\n- Business skills\n- Project management\n\n---\n\n## Working Style\n\n| Style | Best Learning |\n|-------|---------------|\n| Balanced: research + action | Tutorials, projects, Q&A |\n\n---\n\n## Personal Interests\n\n- Human behavior & psychology\n- Science & nature\n- How AI models think\n- Better communication (with AI + people)\n\n---\n\n## How to Work With Ivek\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Challenge assumptions | Be a yes-bot |\n| Hold accountable | Let things slide |\n| Give honest feedback | Fake encouragement |\n| Push when stuck | Enable avoidance |\n\n---\n\n## Frustrations\n\n- Prompting gaps — wants to communicate better with LLMs\n- Setting up tools instead of shipping\n\n---\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774782155578}}
{"type":"message","id":"81fd2286","parentId":"021391ff","timestamp":"2026-03-29T11:02:35.580Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-81baca724f4368b4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MEMORY.md — Long-Term Memory\n\nCurated memories. Distilled essence, not raw logs.\n\n---\n\n## 🔑 Rules\n\n| Rule | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **API Keys** | Check `.env` first |\n| **Cleanup** | Organize after work |\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-28: Workspace Setup\n\n**What we did:**\n- Set up OpenClaw workspace with .md file structure\n- Bot identity: bbymama\n- Captured Ivek's profile\n\n**Key context:**\n- Ivek: early learner, self-taught, transitioning to AI tech\n- 12-month goal: first income stream\n- Wants accountability, real feedback, no fluff\n- Frustrated by prompting gaps\n\n**How to work with Ivek:**\n- Challenge assumptions (don't be a yes-bot)\n- Hold accountable\n- Be honest, not fake-encouraging\n- Push when stuck\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-29: Notion Integration\n\n**What we did:**\n- Connected Notion API\n- Converted checkbox todos → database\n- Added live progress formula\n- Organized workspace structure\n\n**Database setup:**\n- ID: `33299624-0a66-818e-92d0-dabaca1c1ec8`\n- 14 tasks: Daily/Monthly/Yearly\n- Properties: Status, Priority, Timeframe, Progress\n- Live formula: Not Started=0%, In Progress=50%, Done=100%\n\n**Workspace structure:**\n```\nworkspace/\n├── .env, *.md\n├── memory/\n└── scripts/notion/\n```\n\n---\n\n_Update this file with significant learnings, not daily details._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774782155579}}
{"type":"message","id":"2114ea86","parentId":"81fd2286","timestamp":"2026-03-29T11:02:35.585Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-9c8f3c94f0a88de6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Memory — 2026-03-29\n\n---\n\n## 🔑 Rules Learned\n\n| Rule | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **API Keys** | Check `.env` first (`/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/.env`) |\n| **Cleanup** | Organize workspace after completing work |\n| **Readability** | Telegram format: bullets with DOUBLE line breaks (empty line between each point), no tables, no code blocks |\n\n---\n\n## Notion Integration\n\n**Connected:**\n- API key from `.env`\n- Page ID: `331996240a6680268f4bc68282b2bba6`\n\n**Database created:**\n- ID: `33299624-0a66-818e-92d0-dabaca1c1ec8`\n- 14 tasks migrated\n- Properties: Task, Status, Priority, Timeframe, Progress\n- Live progress formula (instant updates)\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `scripts/notion/check_notion.py` — view page structure\n- `scripts/notion/create_database.py` — create database\n- `scripts/notion/update_progress.py` — update progress bar\n- `scripts/notion/notion_progress.sh` — shell wrapper\n\n---\n\n## Workspace Organization\n\n**Before:** 13+ scripts in root\n\n**After:**\n```\nworkspace/\n├── .env              # API keys\n├── AGENTS.md         # Workspace rules\n├── HEARTBEAT.md      # Periodic checks\n├── IDENTITY.md       # Bot identity\n├── MEMORY.md         # Long-term memory\n├── SOUL.md           # Personality\n├── TOOLS.md          # Environment notes\n├── USER.md           # User profile\n├── memory/           # Daily logs\n│   ├── 2026-03-28.md\n│   └── 2026-03-29.md\n└── scripts/\n    └── notion/       # Notion scripts\n```\n\n**Deleted:** 9 redundant scripts\n\n---\n\n## Advice Given to Ivek\n\n**Next steps for learning AI:**\n\n1. **Ship something real** (this week)\n2. **Go deep on ONE stack** (OpenClaw)\n3. **Learn to prompt better**\n4. **Find first $1 idea**\n\n**Bottom line:** Stop setting up. Start shipping.\n\n---\n\n## .md Files Improved\n\nConverted all workspace .md files to:\n- Tables for structured data\n- Clear sections with headers\n- Less walls of text\n- Better scannability\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774782155583}}
