nt: “help me move my OpenClaw agents to Hugging Face models” and link the blog post\n\n**Bottom line:** You can keep your OpenClaw agents running affordably and privately by switching to open HF models\n\nBut need blank line after each bullet, meaning after each bullet line we put an empty line. So pattern:\n\n• text\n\n(blank line)\n\nThus we will output:\n\n**Hugging Face Blog Summary – Liberate Your OpenClaw**\n\n• Anthropic limiting Claude access on open agent platforms for Pro/Max users\n\n• Alternative: use open models via Hugging Face Inference Providers\n\n... etc.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"**Hugging"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let's produce final.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Face Blog Summary – Liberate Your OpenClaw**\n\n• Anthropic limiting Claude access on open agent platforms for Pro/Max users\n\n• Alternative: use open models via Hugging Face Inference Providers\n\n• Alternative: run fully local open models on your own hardware\n\n• Hosted route (HF Inference Providers) is fastest to get capable agents back\n\n• Local route offers privacy, zero API cost, full control\n\n• To switch, tell your agent: “help me move my OpenClaw agents to Hugging Face models” and link the blog post\n\n**Bottom line:** You can keep your OpenClaw agents running affordably and privately by switching to open HF models."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":29352,"output":685,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30037,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774782836199,"responseId":"chatcmpl-8f272aef1549c1ec"}}
