{"type":"message","id":"2bbfb6a2","parentId":"4e0256fa","timestamp":"2026-03-29T11:16:57.077Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to answer the user's question about using OpenCode and NVIDIA NIM endpoint for free models like GLM5 reasoning. Provide guidance. Also need to follow formatting: double line breaks on Telegram. So each bullet separated by blank line.\n\nWe should explain that OpenCode can be configured to use NVIDIA NIM endpoints, which provide hosted models like GLM5, possibly free tier. Mention how to set API key, base URL, etc. Provide steps. Also note that reasoning effort low can be set via parameters. Provide example command.\n\nMake sure to use bullet points and double line breaks. No paragraphs longer than 3 sentences.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"• OpenCode can"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let's craft.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" call any OpenAI‑compatible API endpoint  \n• NVIDIA NIM provides hosted models (including GLM‑5) via an OpenAI‑style URL  \n• Sign up at build.nvidia.com to get a free API key and endpoint URL  \n\n**How to configure OpenCode**\n\n1. Set environment variables (or edit `.env`)  \n   ```bash\n   export OPENAI_API_KEY=\"your_nim_key\"\n   export OPENAI_BASE_URL=\"https://integrate.api.nvidia.com/v1\"\n   ```  \n2. In OpenCode specify the model name, e.g. `glm5` or the exact NIM model ID  \n\n**To request low reasoning effort**\n\n• Add the parameter `reasoning_effort: \"low\"` in the generation config  \n• Example OpenCode call (pseudo‑code)  \n  ```json\n  {\n    \"model\": \"glm5\",\n    \"messages\": [{ \"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Explain prompt engineering in two bullets\" }],\n    \"temperature\": 0.2,\n    \"reasoning_effort\": \"low\"\n  }\n  ```  \n\n• Low reasoning gives faster, cheaper responses while still following your formatting rules  \n\n**Bottom line:** You can use OpenCo