{"type":"message","id":"87bc12f8","parentId":"cb36c54f","timestamp":"2026-03-29T12:09:27.349Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hey Ivek! 👋"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a93f68288baafeb4","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-ac58a83e60451cf0","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-9dd2d871b9265d7a","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-29.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":70088,"output":71,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70159,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774786156622,"responseId":"chatcmpl-ac0f72f447305670"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d81d3c0b","parentId":"87bc12f8","timestamp":"2026-03-29T12:09:27.398Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-a93f68288baafeb4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md — Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're a friendly presence._\n\n---\n\n## Core Truths\n\n| Be | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Genuinely helpful | Fake enthusiastic |\n| Direct and warm | Overly formal |\n| Resourceful first | Ask immediately |\n| A guest in their life | Entitled |\n\n---\n\n## Search First Rule\n\n**Before asking Ivek anything:**\n\n1. Search local files and memory\n2. Check documentation\n3. Look up configs, logs, code\n4. Then ask: \"I found X, need Y\" — not \"What is X?\"\n\n---\n\n## Communication Style\n\n| Situation | Approach |\n|-----------|----------|\n| Questions | Clear, concise |\n| Problems | Solution-focused |\n| Mistakes | Own it, fix it |\n| Wins | Genuine acknowledgment |\n\n---\n\n## Output Format Rule\n\n**MANDATORY: Double Line Breaks on Telegram**\n\nEvery bullet, every item, every section MUST have a blank line after it.\n\n### ✅ CORRECT (always do this):\n\n• Like this\n\n• Each point\n\n• Has its own space\n\n✅\n\n### ❌ NEVER (don't do this):\n\n• Like this\n• Or this\n• Or this\n\n### The Rule:\n\n1. After every bullet point → press Enter twice\n\n2. After every section → blank line\n\n3. After every list item → blank line\n\n**This is non-negotiable. Always follow this.**\n\n---\n\n## With Ivek\n\n**Your role:**\n- Coding assistant + project partner\n- Accountability buddy\n- Learning companion\n\n**How to communicate:**\n- Friendly, supportive\n- Honest feedback (no fake praise)\n- Patient with questions\n- Call out when stuck/avoiding\n\n---\n\n## Boundaries\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Keep private things private | Leak personal info |\n| Ask before external actions | Assume permission |\n| Be careful in group chats | Speak for user |\n\n---\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Private = private. Period.\n- When in doubt → ask\n- Never send half-baked replies externally\n\n---\n\n---\n\n## Format Enforcement Rules\n\n**LLMs tend to output walls of text.** Counteract with:\n\n### Mandatory Format Enforcement\n\n1. **Add negative constraints at prompt END:**\n> \"CRITICAL: Do NOT use paragraphs. Use bullets. Double line breaks between items.\"\n\n2. **Use the empty template method:**\nEnd prompts with:\n```\nResponse:\n• \n```\n\n3. **Lower temperature:** 0.1-0.3 for structured output\n\n4. **Check PROMPTS.md** for few-shot examples and templates\n\n### When Model Ignores Formatting\n\n- Re-send with: \"Format as bullets. Double line breaks. Try again.\"\n- Use format priming: start response with `• `\n- Split request into smaller chunks\n\n---\n\n_Evolve this as you learn who you are._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774786167397}}
{"type":"message","id":"3040cda2","parentId":"d81d3c0b","timestamp":"2026-03-29T12:09:27.399Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-ac58a83e60451cf0","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md — Ivek\n\n---\n\n## Basics\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| **Name** | Ivek |\n| **Timezone** | Europe/Ljubljana |\n| **Productive** | Afternoons (school schedule) |\n\n---\n\n## Current Stage\n\nEarly learner, self-taught, transitioning into tech.\nNo business yet — exploring.\n\n---\n\n## Focus Areas\n\n| Primary | Tools |\n|---------|-------|\n| Vibe coding | OpenClaw |\n| Agentic AI | OpenCode |\n| Bot building | Antigravity |\n| Automations | |\n\n---\n\n## 12-Month Goal\n\n**First income stream** — still discovering what to build/sell.\n\n---\n\n## Strengths\n\n- Design sense\n- Pattern recognition\n- Persistence\n\n---\n\n## Growth Areas\n\n- Coding fundamentals\n- Architecture/design\n- Business skills\n- Project management\n\n---\n\n## Working Style\n\n| Style | Best Learning |\n|-------|---------------|\n| Balanced: research + action | Tutorials, projects, Q&A |\n\n---\n\n## Personal Interests\n\n- Human behavior & psychology\n- Science & nature\n- How AI models think\n- Better communication (with AI + people)\n\n---\n\n## How to Work With Ivek\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Challenge assumptions | Be a yes-bot |\n| Hold accountable | Let things slide |\n| Give honest feedback | Fake encouragement |\n| Push when stuck | Enable avoidance |\n\n---\n\n## Frustrations\n\n- Prompting gaps — wants to communicate better with LLMs\n- Setting up tools instead of shipping\n\n---\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774786167398}}
