{"type":"message","id":"d549d4ca","parentId":"3fce22a2","timestamp":"2026-03-29T12:41:42.726Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says the mini course looks amazing. They likely want to continue or maybe they are satisfied. We should ask what they want to do next. However we need to follow the output format: double line breaks after each bullet/item/section. We must not use paragraphs without breaks. We'll respond with bullet points and double line breaks.\n\nWe'll say something like: • Glad you like it! • What would you like to do next? Then maybe list options. Ensure double line breaks between each bullet.\n\nWe'll output:\n\n• Glad you like the mini course!\n\n• What would you like to work on next?\n  • Add more resources to the CLI Agents database\n  • Start building the AI‑digest service (daily AI news via Telegram)\n  • Sketch a monetization plan for the prompt engineering course\n  • Something else?\n\nWe need double line breaks after each bullet point. However sub-bullets? The format says every bullet, every item, every section must have a blank line after it. So we need to have top-level bullets, and after each top-level bullet we need a blank line. Sub-bullets maybe considered items? To be safe, we can keep it simple: just top-level bullets each separated by a blank line.\n\nWe'll do:\n\n• Glad you like the mini course!\n\n• What would you like to work on next?\n  • Add more resources to the CLI Agents database\n  • Start building the AI‑digest service (daily AI news via Telegram)\n  • Sketch a monetization plan for the prompt engineering course\n  • Something else?\n\nBut then we have nested bullets. Might be okay but we need double line breaks after each bullet item. To avoid complexity, we can just list options as separate top-level bullets.\n\nLet's produce:\n\n• Glad you like the mini course!\n\n• What would you like to work on next?\n• Add more resources to the CLI Agents database\n• Start building the AI‑digest service (daily AI news via Telegram)\n• Sketch a monetization plan for the prompt engineering course\n• Something else?\n\nBut that loses grouping. Could also do:\n\n• Glad you like the mini course!\n• What would you like to work on next?\n  – Add more resources to the CLI Agents database\n  – Start building the AI‑digest service (daily AI news via Telegram)\n  – Sketch a monetization plan for the prompt engineering course\n  – Something else?\n\nBut we need to ensure double line breaks after each bullet. The nested dash might be considered a bullet? Safer to avoid nested.\n\nWe'll do top-level bullets only. We'll ask an open-ended question and list options as separate bullets.\n\nThus:\n\n• Glad you like the mini course!\n\n• What would you like to work on next?\n• Add more resources to the CLI Agents database\n• Start building the AI‑digest service (daily AI news via Telegram)\n• Sketch a monetization plan for the prompt engineering course\n• Something else?\n\nBut the second bullet is a question, then we list options. Could combine: \"What would you like to work on next? Choose from:\" then list.\n\nBetter:\n\n• Glad you like the mini course!\n\n• What would you like to work on next? Choose one:\n• Add more resources to the CLI Agents database\n• Start building the AI‑digest service (daily AI news via Telegram)\n• Sketch a monetization plan for the prompt engineering course\n• Something else?\n\nWe need double line breaks after each line. We'll output exactly that with blank lines between each bullet","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"• Glad you like"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":".\n\nLet's craft.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" the mini course!\n\n• What would you like to work on next? Choose one:\n• Add more resources to the CLI Agents database\n• Start building the AI‑digest service (daily AI news via Telegram)\n• Sketch a monetization plan for the prompt engineering course\n• Somet