{"type":"message","id":"b79f40b3","parentId":"2a0ca67c","timestamp":"2026-03-29T12:44:29.957Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to produce three monetization ideas for prompt engineering based on current research. Provide them as bullet points with double line breaks, following the format rules. Should be concise and actionable. Let's craft three ideas:\n\n1. Sell a prompt library/template pack for specific niches (e.g., marketing copy, coding helpers, academic writing) via Gumroad or Etsy.\n2. Offer a prompt engineering consulting/service: audit and improve clients' prompts, provide custom prompt sets, with tiered pricing (starter, pro, enterprise).\n3. Create a paid newsletter or subscription (Substack) delivering weekly prompt packs, tips, and case studies; monetize via paid tiers.\n\nWe'll also maybe reference the market size from the search. Provide as bullets.\n\nNow produce answer with double line breaks.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n• **Niche Prompt Template Packs**  \n  – Create and sell curated prompt bundles for high‑demand use cases (e.g., LinkedIn content generators, SEO blog outlines, SQL query builders, customer‑support chat scripts)  \n  – Price each pack $10‑$30 on Gumroad/Etsy; include a short guide, example outputs, and a Notion template for users to save their own variations  \n  – Validate demand by checking search volume for “best prompts for [niche]” and offering a free mini‑sample to collect emails  \n\n• **Prompt Engineering Consulting & Custom Prompt Sets**  \n  – Offer a service where you audit a client’s current prompts, identify gaps, and deliver a tailored prompt library + quick‑start guide  \n  – Tiered pricing: Starter ($150 for 5 prompts + guide), Pro ($400 for 15 prompts + 30‑min call), Enterprise ($1000+ for ongoing prompt‑maintenance and team training)  \n  – Leverage your mini‑course as a lead magnet; promote via LinkedIn, Indie Hackers, and relevant Discord/Telegram groups  \n\n• **Paid Prompt‑of‑the‑Week Newsletter (Substack/Beehiiv)**  \n  – Weekly issue delivers one battle‑tested prompt, a breakdown of why it works, a variation for different tones/formats, and a micro‑challenge for readers  \n  – Free tier gets monthly summary; paid tier ($5/month or $50/year) gets full weekly prompts, access to an archive, and a private community for feedback  \n  – Growth tactics: cross‑post snippets on Twitter/X with a call‑to‑action, collaborate with AI‑tool affiliates, and offer a referral discount for bringing friends  \n\n**Bottom line:** Combine low‑cost digital products (template packs), high‑touch services (consulting), and recurring revenue (newsletter) to test what resonates fastest and scale the winner. Let me know which idea you’d like to prototype first, or if you want to add more resources to the CLI database or start the AI‑digest service instead."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":94686,"output":632,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95318,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774788229235,"responseId":"chatcmpl-a76c21e2f84f66f9"}}
