{"type":"message","id":"1559db78","parentId":"4edbcaf5","timestamp":"2026-03-29T15:31:33.284Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-849151fdc0cfe4a8","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# How I Run 8 AI Employees 24/7 with OpenClaw - Multi-Agent Setup for Beginners\n**URL:** https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CYBZmwOmsk8\n**Channel:** Sonny Sangha\n**Published:** 2026-03-26\n**Duration:** 26:11\n\n## Statistics\n- Views: 15,041\n- Likes: 253\n- Comments: 13\n\n## Technical Details\n- Definition: HD\n- Dimension: 2d\n- Projection: rectangular\n- Has Captions: No\n- Licensed Content: Yes\n\n**Tags:** react, developer, reactjs, html, css, js, javascript, papa, papareact, papa-react\n\n## Description\n️❗️Set up your OpenClaw Bot here & Use code SONNY for 10% off 👉 https://hostinger.com/sonnyopenclaw\n🚀 Join the Zero to OpenClaw Hero waitlist 👉 https://www.papareact.com/ztoh-form\n\nOne AI agent doing everything is like hiring one person to be your copywriter, developer, researcher, and project manager — eventually the context window fills up, things get forgotten, and mistakes pile up.\n\nThis video shows you exactly how to build your first multi-agent AI team with OpenClaw so each agent specializes in what it does best.\n\nOpenClaw lets you run multiple AI agents on a single server, each with their own memory, personality, skills, and model — all orchestrated by one main agent. Instead of bloating one agent with every tool imaginable, you split responsibilities so each agent stays sharp and focused.\n\nI'll walk you through creating your second agent from scratch, wiring it up to Telegram, installing skills, and having your main agent delegate tasks automatically — all running 24/7 on a Hostinger VPS.\n\nWe'll cover:\n✅ Why one agent isn't enough (context windows and bloat)\n✅ How OpenClaw workspaces isolate each agent's memory and identity\n✅ Creating a new agent (Ink) via the CLI and connecting it to Telegram\n✅ Installing agent-specific skills from skills.sh (social content writing)\n✅ Sub-agents vs multi-agent routing — when to use each\n✅ Training your main agent to orchestrate and delegate tasks\n✅ Live demo: Ink vs Neo writing the same Instagram post\n✅ Do's and don'ts: model selection, when to add agents, and the golden rules\n\nStart with one agent, master it, then grow your team only when you hit friction. That's the golden rule.\n\n🕣 TIMESTAMPS:\n0:00 Intro — Why You Need an AI Agent Team\n1:57 Why Multi-Agent Beats Single Agent\n2:09 Hostinger VPS & OpenClaw Setup\n3:53 Memory System Explained\n4:13 Key Files: Identity, Soul & Memory\n5:13 Creating a New Agent (Ink)\n6:56 Auth Profiles & API Keys\n7:11 Choosing a Model for Your Agent\n7:54 Connecting Agents to Channels\n8:11 What Happens Under the Hood\n9:12 Setting Up Telegram for Ink\n16:12 Installing Skills for Agents\n17:52 How Skills Match & Load\n18:18 Sub-Agents vs Multi-Agent Routing\n20:07 First Multi-Agent Task Demo\n21:15 Comparing Ink vs Neo Output\n21:54 Do's & Don'ts for Multi-Agent Setup\n22:58 Model Selection Tips (Save Money)\n23:10 Don't Create Too Many Agents\n23:52 Why VPS Matters\n24:28 Sonny's 8-Agent Team Overview\n25:37 Recap & Golden Rules\n\n⸻\n\n⚠️ DISCLAIMER: This video is sponsored by Hostinger. All opinions are my own — I only share tools I personally use and believe will help the developer community.\n\n📜 Copyright Disclaimer: This video is made for informational and educational purposes only. Copyright Disclaimer under Section 107 of the Copyright Act 1976 allows \"fair use\" for educational purposes.\n\n——————\n🎓 Learn to code with AI here: https://www.papareact.com/course\n👥 Join our AI coding community for FREE: https://www.universityofcode.com\n\nFollow me on socials:\n🔗 Instagram: https://instagram.com/sonnysangha\n🔗 Twitter/X: https://x.com/sonnysangha\n🔗 LinkedIn: https://linkedin.com/in/sonnysangha\n🔗 TikTok: https://tiktok.com/@sonnysangha"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durat