ting the same Instagram post\n✅ Do's and don'ts: model selection, when to add agents, and the golden rules\n\nStart with one agent, master it, then grow your team only when you hit friction. That's the golden rule.\n\n🕣 TIMESTAMPS:\n0:00 Intro — Why You Need an AI Agent Team\n1:57 Why Multi-Agent Beats Single Agent\n2:09 Hostinger VPS & OpenClaw Setup\n3:53 Memory System Explained\n4:13 Key Files: Identity, Soul & Memory\n5:13 Creating a New Agent (Ink)\n6:56 Auth Profiles & API Keys\n7:11 Choosing a Model for Your Agent\n7:54 Connecting Agents to Channels\n8:11 What Happens Under the Hood\n9:12 Setting Up Telegram for Ink\n16:12 Installing Skills for Agents\n17:52 How Skills Match & Load\n18:18 Sub-Agents vs Multi-Agent Routing\n20:07 First Multi-Agent Task Demo\n21:15 Comparing Ink vs Neo Output\n21:54 Do's & Don'ts for Multi-Agent Setup\n22:58 Model Selection Tips (Save Money)\n23:10 Don't Create Too Many Agents\n23:52 Why VPS Matters\n24:28 Sonny's 8-Agent Team Overview\n25:37 Recap & Golden Rules\n\n⸻\n\n⚠️ DISCLAIMER: This video is sponsored by Hostinger. All opinions are my own — I only share tools I personally use and believe will help the developer community.\n\n📜 Copyright Disclaimer: This video is made for informational and educational purposes only. Copyright Disclaimer under Section 107 of the Copyright Act 1976 allows \"fair use\" for educational purposes.\n\n——————\n🎓 Learn to code with AI here: https://www.papareact.com/course\n👥 Join our AI coding community for FREE: https://www.universityofcode.com\n\nFollow me on socials:\n🔗 Instagram: https://instagram.com/sonnysangha\n🔗 Twitter/X: https://x.com/sonnysangha\n🔗 LinkedIn: https://linkedin.com/in/sonnysangha\n🔗 TikTok: https://tiktok.com/@sonnysangha","cwd":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774798293273}}
