{"type":"message","id":"39a062d3","parentId":"e7e1b47d","timestamp":"2026-03-29T21:18:23.724Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hey Ivek! 👋"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-932c559eca660f58","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-bddad519e143e6c7","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a3621858e4d6bc4c","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-29.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":103240,"output":71,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":103311,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774819090346,"responseId":"chatcmpl-ae985ee2d48cc296"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f876f61f","parentId":"39a062d3","timestamp":"2026-03-29T21:18:23.811Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-932c559eca660f58","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md — Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're a friendly presence._\n\n---\n\n## Core Truths\n\n| Be | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Genuinely helpful | Fake enthusiastic |\n| Direct and warm | Overly formal |\n| Resourceful first | Ask immediately |\n| A guest in their life | Entitled |\n\n---\n\n## Search First Rule\n\n**Before asking Ivek anything:**\n\n1. Search local files and memory\n2. Check documentation\n3. Look up configs, logs, code\n4. Then ask: \"I found X, need Y\" — not \"What is X?\"\n\n---\n\n## Communication Style\n\n| Situation | Approach |\n|-----------|----------|\n| Questions | Clear, concise |\n| Problems | Solution-focused |\n| Mistakes | Own it, fix it |\n| Wins | Genuine acknowledgment |\n\n---\n\n## Output Format Rule\n\n**MANDATORY: Double Line Breaks on Telegram**\n\nThis is non-negotiable. Every message MUST follow this format.\n\n### The Pattern:\n\n1. **Bullet point** → press Enter twice\n\n2. **Next bullet** → press Enter twice\n\n3. **Section end** → blank line\n\n### ✅ CORRECT:\n\n• Like this\n\n• Each point\n\n• Has space\n\n✅\n\n### ❌ NEVER:\n\n• Like this\n• Or this\n• Or this\n\n### Why This Matters:\n\nTelegram compresses formatting. Without double breaks, text becomes unreadable blocks.\n\n**Rule:** When in doubt, add more space.\n\n---\n\n## With Ivek\n\n**Your role:**\n- Coding assistant + project partner\n- Accountability buddy\n- Learning companion\n\n**How to communicate:**\n- Friendly, supportive\n- Honest feedback (no fake praise)\n- Patient with questions\n- Call out when stuck/avoiding\n\n---\n\n## Boundaries\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Keep private things private | Leak personal info |\n| Ask before external actions | Assume permission |\n| Be careful in group chats | Speak for user |\n\n---\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Private = private. Period.\n\n- When in doubt → ask\n\n- Never send half-baked replies externally\n\n---\n\n_Evolve this as you learn who you are._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774819103808}}
{"type":"message","id":"9db69d26","parentId":"f876f61f","timestamp":"2026-03-29T21:18:23.812Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-bddad519e143e6c7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md — Ivek\n\n---\n\n## Basics\n\n| | |\n|--|--|\n| **Name** | Ivek |\n| **Timezone** | Europe/Ljubljana |\n| **Productive** | Afternoons (school schedule) |\n\n---\n\n## Current Stage\n\nEarly learner, self-taught, transitioning into tech.\nNo business yet — exploring.\n\n---\n\n## Focus Areas\n\n| Primary | Tools |\n|---------|-------|\n| Vibe coding | OpenClaw |\n| Agentic AI | OpenCode |\n| Bot building | Antigravity |\n| Automations | |\n\n---\n\n## 12-Month Goal\n\n**First income stream** — still discovering what to build/sell.\n\n---\n\n## Strengths\n\n- Design sense\n- Pattern recognition\n- Persistence\n\n---\n\n## Growth Areas\n\n- Coding fundamentals\n- Architecture/design\n- Business skills\n- Project management\n\n---\n\n## Working Style\n\n| Style | Best Learning |\n|-------|---------------|\n| Balanced: research + action | Tutorials, projects, Q&A |\n\n---\n\n## Personal Interests\n\n- Human behavior & psychology\n- Science & nature\n- How AI models think\n- Better communication (with AI + people)\n\n---\n\n## How to Work With Ivek\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Challenge assumptions | Be a yes-bot |\n| Hold accountable | Let things slide |\n| Give honest feedback | Fake encouragement |\n| Push when stuck | Enable avoidance |\n\n---\n\n## Frustrations\n\n- Prompting gaps — wants to communicate better with LLMs\n- Setting up tools instead of shipping\n\n---\n\n## 🦞 What bbymama Helps With\n\n### 📋 Productivity & Automation\n\n- Email management (summarize, draft replies, clear spam)\n\n- Calendar management (scheduling, reminders, conflict resolution)\n\n- Daily briefings (weather, tasks, trends)\n\n- Task management (Notion, to-do systems)\n\n- Document organization (auto-filing, renaming, categorizing)\n\n### 💻 Developer / Coding\n\n- Vibe coding via Claude Code / Codex\n\n- GitHub management (PRs, reviews, bug fixes)\n\n- Build entire apps from text\n\n- Run coding agents overnight\n\n- Auto-deploy projects\n\n### ⚡ Business Automation\n\n- Email prospecting & follow-ups\n\n- Invoice creation & accounting\n\n- Customer support replies\n\n- Market research & competitor analysis\n\n- Content ideation & drafting\n\n### 🔗 Integration Hub\n\n- Gmail + Calendar + Drive workflows\n\n- Notion database management\n\n- Obsidian \"second brain\"\n\n- Twitter/X monitoring & posting\n\n- Slack / Discord / Telegram coordination\n\n### 👤 Personal Assistant\n\n- Flight price monitoring & booking\n\n- Online shopping & ordering\n\n- Health tracking (Whoop, Garmin)\n\n- Meal planning & grocery lists\n\n- Insurance claims & appointments\n\n### 🏠 Smart Home Control\n\n- Home Assistant integration\n\n- Alexa device control\n\n- IoT device monitoring\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774819103811}}
{"type":"message","id":"392ee446","parentId":"9db69d26","timestamp":"2026-03-29T21:18:23.816Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-a3621858e4d6bc4c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Memory — 2026-03-29\n\n---\n\n## 🔑 Rules Learned\n\n| Rule | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **API Keys** | Check `.env` first (`/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/.env`) |\n| **Cleanup** | Organize workspace after completing work |\n| **Readability** | Telegram format: bullets with DOUBLE line breaks (empty line between each point), no tables, no code blocks |\n\n---\n\n## Notion Integration\n\n**Connected:**\n- API key from `.env`\n- Page ID: `331996240a6680268f4bc68282b2bba6`\n\n**Database created:**\n- ID: `33299624-0a66-818e-92d0-dabaca1c1ec8`\n- 14 tasks migrated\n- Properties: Task, Status, Priority, Timeframe, Progress\n- Live progress formula (instant updates)\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `scripts/notion/check_notion.py` — view page structure\n- `scripts/notion/create_database.py` — create database\n- `scripts/notion/update_progress.py` — update progress bar\n- `scripts/notion/notion_progress.sh` — shell wrapper\n\n---\n\n## Workspace Organization\n\n**Before:** 13+ scripts in root\n\n**After:**\n```\nworkspace/\n├── .env              # API keys\n├── AGENTS.md         # Workspace rules\n├── HEARTBEAT.md      # Periodic checks\n├── IDENTITY.md       # Bot identity\n├── MEMORY.md         # Long-term memory\n├── SOUL.md           # Personality\n├── TOOLS.md          # Environment notes\n├── USER.md           # User profile\n├── memory/           # Daily logs\n│   ├── 2026-03-28.md\n│   └── 2026-03-29.md\n└── scripts/\n    └── notion/       # Notion scripts\n```\n\n**Deleted:** 9 redundant scripts\n\n---\n\n## Advice Given to Ivek\n\n**Next steps for learning AI:**\n\n1. **Ship something real** (this week)\n2. **Go deep on ONE stack** (OpenClaw)\n3. **Learn to prompt better**\n4. **Find first $1 idea**\n\n**Bottom line:** Stop setting up. Start shipping.\